##Wuhan, these days the streets and alleys (II) 

Weiweiao999

Introduction, hello, I am Li Wei Ao, thank you for your attention. Note: It may take a month or two to update this post, or even longer

A week ago, I wrote Wuhan, the streets these days, and many friends said it was interesting and meaningful to me, as if I were a person in Wuhan, because they stayed at home and didn't go out much, and I still drove every day, walking around the city.

I decided to continue writing on the subject, as I saw and heard on the streets of Wuhan.

Originally wanted to write the past week, the result, in a hurry to organize, just three days of pictures, it is quite a lot.

So, for today, write about the period from February 18 to February 20.

Like last time, some of the pictures here were taken by dslr camera, and some were only taken by mobile phone "quietly" ..

February 18,2020

From this day on, the control of Wuhan was suddenly upgraded.

For one, Wuchang District's rules do not allow supermarkets to be open to individual customers, but only to community groups.

We saw this in front of the Hongshan Square store in Carrefour, Wuhan.

At the same time, in the twenty minutes or so that we have been here, we have seen four or five uninformed individual customers who have not been allowed in.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In order to send her to the medical staff at Wuhan's Central Hospital as a result of her long-term wearing of gloves, she had to buy a lot of hand cream and body lotions, and heavy use of alcohol and hand Sanitizer, hand cream was in high demand, as we headed to Carrefour's ten-litre store in Hanyang District.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(individual customers are welcome, but only if there is a stamped "road" -- a resident's pass.)

We explained the situation to the head of the store, got his understanding and support, here bought 339(bottles) hand cream, lotion, packed seven boxes; then, sent to the Wuhan Central Hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fresh meat, still in short supply in Wuhan, is generally available only in the morning

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The old man came to the supermarket by himself. The shopkeeper said there were fewer customers in the store that day than the day before

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(we delivered seven boxes of 339 hand creams and Lotions to Wuhan Central Hospital that afternoon. Another friend contacted other donors and donated 1,000 hand creams to another hospital, called the Tongji Hospital in Wuhan. "You protect the world, I protect you, " read the package. Not only hand cream, several of my friends, through the voluntary fund-raising between acquaintances, raised more than 200,000 yuan, these days, for several hospitals in Wuhan, purchased hundreds of protective clothing, but also gave them the box to work overtime, as if the national crisis, money, power, every citizen is working hard

19 February

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(on February 19th the mini-mart, on the East road of the martial arts exhibition, is still able to take individual customers, but has to take their temperature and queue into the store as if to control the number of customers, including police officers waiting outside) 

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(it was also a bicycle shopper on the East road of the show, falling to the ground and struggling to pick it up, as I've seen several times in recent days...) 

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Mr. Rice" , a fast-food restaurant on Jiefang Avenue, is not for sale to individuals, but only to the opposite Wuhan Union Hospital, the staff said

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(outside Mr. Rice's, hummingbird players wait to deliver meals to the hospital, their clothes labeled "temperature normal today. ")

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The scavengers on Jinghan Avenue and Wuzhan East road may not have much to pick up these days

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(on Jinghan Avenue, the old man's lunch seemed to be better. I wondered: What kind of person is he? Where did he get this lunch...)

Compared with the old man who can eat on the bench, the policeman on duty outside a quarantine point on the long Sheng road can only eat his dinner standing up

(the Tam Giang Space Hotel on long ascension road has been commandeered as a "quarantine point" . Residents nearby said two buses had arrived the day before, Feb. 18, and had taken many people from the area, either to a shelter or to another hospital

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(on the opposite side of the Tam Giang Space Hotel, Florida Gutian apartments, labeled "infected area")

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(outside Gutian's apartment, a pile of paper money, still smoldering, was burned for whom? And what was the cause of death...)

20 February

On February 20, we went to the warehouse of Wuhan Red Cross in Foshan, the center of Wuhan National Museum.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(less than 1 / 10 of the supplies donated here are now available, compared with more than 10 days ago. "We can do the same-day delivery, " the staff said.)

It was hard for Wuhan to get the Wuhan Red Cross to do the receiving and distribution of donations in the first place -- it was like 100 times as much, or more, in this warehouse as it is today, at the height of the rush. The Red Cross is neither a professional warehousing, logistics and Distribution Organization, nor a very small number of people.

The next time there is a catastrophe in China, it is worth thinking about who will be responsible for receiving and distributing the goods

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Donation from Macau, China

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(not long after we saw donations from Daegu, South Korea, there was a new outbreak of pneumonia in Daegu, and on February 25th South Korean President Moon jae-in went to Taegu.)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There is also a "shelter hospital" at the Guobo Center in Wuhan

Waiting for the bus, the paramedic gossips about today's incident:

"I asked a patient, 'who do you miss? ' And he said, 'I miss you. ' I laughed and said, 'hey, don't joke with us about medicine, you're not going to be able to stand it... ' "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Walking along the river road, I saw a man with limited mobility. He was pushing his wheelchair backwards on his two legs

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(one block in Wuhan is all named after a place in Taiwan, such as Kaohsiung Road and Miaoli road. Kaohsiung Road also has an isolation point.)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Kaohsiung Road, to the 20th This Day, the small supermarket is not for individual business, must be community group purchase

Two young men came to the door, but couldn't buy anything. "This is ridiculous, " they complained. "We're here, and they want us to go back to group buying... "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(about 20 metres from the supermarket, on Huiji District road, a cyclist charges his electric bike while talking on the phone:

"group buying, group buying, you know what I mean? You can't buy something for one person, you have to organize it in the community... oh, this group buying is very expensive, 100,200 a bag of vegetables, but it's good to be able to buy it... ")

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hualien Community Party Service Center staff, saw me in the photo, suddenly very nervous and said to me, "my phone is charging, charging Ah, these days (phone) have been shot... "

These days, Wuhan's prevention and Control Management is tighter and tighter, whether a considerable part of the work task, or even most of it, is transmitted to the most basic staff..

Though he is young, he is willing to be a good memory
